.I val div 
: 
.B int64 -> int64 -> int64
.sp
Integer division\&.  Raise 
.B Division_by_zero
if the second
argument is zero\&.  This division rounds the real quotient of
its arguments towards zero, as specified for 
.B Pervasives\&.(/)
\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val rem 
: 
.B int64 -> int64 -> int64
.sp
Integer remainder\&.  If 
.B y
is not zero, the result
of 
.B Int64\&.rem x y
satisfies the following property:
.B x = Int64\&.add (Int64\&.mul (Int64\&.div x y) y) (Int64\&.rem x y)
\&.
If 
.B y = 0
, 
.B Int64\&.rem x y
raises 
.B Division_by_zero
\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val succ 
: 
.B int64 -> int64
.sp
Successor\&.  
.B Int64\&.succ x
is 
.B Int64\&.add x Int64\&.one
\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val pred 
: 
.B int64 -> int64
.sp
Predecessor\&.  
.B Int64\&.pred x
is 
.B Int64\&.sub x Int64\&.one
\&.
.sp

